Turkey Steel Melting Capacity 36.6 Million Tons

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-02-17T08:45:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/turkey-steel-melting-capacity-36-6-million-tons-correct-.html
(Corrects 2011 capacity in headline and first
paragraph.)    Turkey ’s steel melting capacity
will increase to 36.6 million metric tons this year from
34.5 million tons in 2010, Veysel Yayan, chairman of the
Turkish steel producers association said.  The country’s crude flat steel output capacity in 2011
will rise to 15.9 million tons from last year’s 13.4
million tons, Yayan said at conference in Istanbul today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
